## Datasets

Datasets of the course will be stored in the Datasets folder in the ILIAS. It is highly recommended to download and save the datasets to a local folder.

### For classroom demonstrations

1.  [Car pricing dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/amjadzhour/car-price-prediction)
2.  [Electricity cost dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shalmamuji/electricity-cost-prediction-dataset)
3.  [Medical insurance dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kanzariachref/medical-insurance-cost-dataset)
4.  [Wallmart sales dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mikhail1681/walmart-sales)
5.  [Salary dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/abhishek14398/salary-dataset-simple-linear-regression)
6.  [Study performance dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/nikhil7280/student-performance-multiple-linear-regression)
7.  Datasets from reference books
8.  And many other

### Popular datasets for social science research

1.  [ESS](https://www.europeansocialsurvey.org/)
2.  [WVS](https://www.worldvaluessurvey.org)

## Teaching method

Lectures, demonstrations and practice during the class

Applying statistical methods in real scenario

Group work, going through a research project from start to finish

Learning tools to apply statistical concepts in real life data

## Exam form and evaluation

The final grade will be a combination of the result from a research project and a classroom examination.

-   **Research project (50% of the final grade):** Theoretical and empirical model including theory, research question/hypotheses, detailed derivation of hypotheses from the literature, methodology, descriptive results, model variables and regression analysis, scientific discussion, literature (minimum requirement: seven scientific references (journal articles), APA citation style), plus submission of dataset and syntax (final evaluations and model) + output regression analysis. Format: Presentation on the last lecture date with PowerPoint presentation and paper (max. 8 pages without appendix)

-   **Individual test (50% of the final grade):** Date and time will be announced later

## Grading

-   Midterm (individual performance): 50%\
    90-minute open book exam\
    (FAQ: Do I have to pass it to get the pass mark for the course?\
    Answer: No.

-   Paper + Group presentation (group evaluation): 50%\
    Students have to pass it!
